    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Pleurothallis spegazziniana are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. These preparations are made from the plant's leaves, stems, and flowers, which contain flavonoids, phenolic acids, and saponins with anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. A tea or infusion of Pleurothallis spegazziniana is prepared by steeping the plant material in hot water, and is traditionally used to treat digestive issues and fever. A tincture is made by soaking the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, and is used to treat respiratory issues and skin conditions. A decoction of the plant is prepared by boiling the plant material in water, and is used to treat urinary tract infections and wounds, while a salve is applied topically to treat skin conditions and wounds.",
